# Add Passkey (WebAuthn) Authentication Support

## Description

This PR adds passwordless authentication to OpenSearch Security using passkeys (WebAuthn/FIDO2). Users can now authenticate using biometric authentication (Touch ID, Face ID, Windows Hello) or hardware security keys (YubiKey, etc.) instead of passwords.

## Changes

### Core Implementation

**New Authentication Backend**:
- `PasskeyAuthenticationBackend` - Main authentication backend
- `WebAuthnManager` - WebAuthn ceremony orchestration
- `OpenSearchPasskeyCredentialRepository` - Credential storage (main security index)
- `InMemoryChallengeStore` - Challenge management with TTL

**REST API Endpoints** (6 new endpoints):
- `POST /_plugins/_security/passkey/registration/options`
- `POST /_plugins/_security/passkey/registration/verify`
- `POST /_plugins/_security/passkey/authentication/options`
- `POST /_plugins/_security/passkey/authentication/verify`
- `POST /_plugins/_security/passkey/credentials/list`
- `DELETE /_plugins/_security/passkey/credentials/{id}`

**Data Models**:
- `PasskeyCredential` - Credential storage model
- `Challenge` - Challenge/nonce management
- `PasskeyAuthenticationConfig` - Configuration model
- `RelyingPartyConfig` - RP configuration

**Security Components**:
- `PasskeyAuditLogger` - Audit logging for all passkey events
- `PasskeyErrorResponse` - Standardized error responses
- Origin validation and RP ID verification
- Signature counter monitoring

### Storage Architecture

Credentials are stored in the main `.opendistro_security` index:
- Document ID: `passkeycredentials`
- Field: `passkeycreds` (Base64-encoded JSON)
- Access pattern: Matches internal users (privileged context)
- No separate index needed

This approach:
- Follows established security plugin patterns
- Avoids threading violations
- Uses `ConfigurationRepository` integration patterns
- Simplifies deployment

