## API Examples

### Registration Flow

```bash
# Step 1: Get registration options
curl -X POST https://localhost:9200/_plugins/_security/passkey/registration/options \
  -u admin:admin \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"username": "alice"}'

# Response includes challenge and WebAuthn options
# User performs WebAuthn ceremony in browser

# Step 2: Verify registration
curl -X POST https://localhost:9200/_plugins/_security/passkey/registration/verify \
  -u admin:admin \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "username": "alice",
    "challengeId": "...",
    "credential": {...},
    "friendlyName": "My YubiKey"
  }'
```

### Authentication Flow

```bash
# Step 1: Get authentication options
curl -X POST https://localhost:9200/_plugins/_security/passkey/authentication/options \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"username": "alice"}'

# Response includes challenge and allowed credentials
# User performs WebAuthn ceremony in browser

# Step 2: Verify authentication
curl -X POST https://localhost:9200/_plugins/_security/passkey/authentication/verify \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "username": "alice",
    "challengeId": "...",
    "assertion": {...}
  }'
```

